{"opencli":"0.1-draft","info":{"title":"Dacpac.Tool","version":"3.0.518","description":"# How use\n\n## Use .NetCore tool for publish .dacpac file\n\n### What's .dacpac\nA data-tier application (DAC) is a logical database management entity that defines all SQL Server objects - such as tables, views, and instance objects - associated with a user's database. It is a self-contained unit of SQL Server database deployment that enables data-tier developers and DBAs to package SQL Server objects into a portable artifact called a DAC package, or .dacpac file. <sup>[See more](https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/sql/relational-databases/data-tier-applications/data-tier-applications?view=sql-server-2017)</sup>\n\n### Requirements\n\n1. .NET Core 8.0+ runtime installed\n\n### Publish .dacpac with .Net tool\n\n####  Install the Dacpac.Tool package \n\n```powershell\n dotnet tool install --global Dacpac.Tool\n```\n\n#### Run tool only with the required parameters\n\n 1. Use case   \n Multi tenant database, your have same schema for multiple client on database server\n\n* Windows autentication (SSPI)\n```powershell\n\ndotnet dacpac publish --dacpath=C:\\artifact\\db\\ --server=mydatabase.server.contoso.com --databasenames='client1;client2;client3;client4'\n```\n* Specific User authentication \n\n```powershell\ndotnet dacpac publish --dacpath=C:\\artifact\\db\\ --server=mydatabase.server.contoso.com --databasenames='client1;client2;client3;client4' --userId=useWithPersmissionForUpdate --password=123455\n\n```\n\n* Parameters    \n\n|Name|Description|Default|\n|-------|-------|-----|\n|dacpath| Directory where the dacpac file is stored| Directory that the tool is running|\n|databasenames | The names of databases that need to be updated|It's requerid not have default|\n|namenattern|Pattern for search file|*.dacpac|\n|UseSspi|Indicates that the windows user should be used|true\n|userId|Database user <sub>Need permissions for schema change</sub>|carioca|\n|password| The password from 'userid' | IFromBrazilian|\n\n[See all parameters](https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/dotnet/api/microsoft.sqlserver.dac.dacdeployoptions?redirectedfrom=MSDN&view=sql-dacfx-140.3881.1)"},"x-inspectra":{"artifactSource":"startup-hook","generator":"InSpectra.Discovery","hookCapture":{"systemCommandLineVersion":"2.0.0.0","patchTarget":"ProcessExit-fallback (OK: ArgumentExtensions.Parse, OK: CommandExtensions.Parse, OK: CommandExtensions.Parse, OK: OptionExtensions.Parse, OK: Parser.Parse, OK: ParserExtensions.Parse, OK: CommandExtensions.Invoke, OK: CommandExtensions.Invoke, OK: ParseResultExtensions.Invoke, OK: ParserExtensions.Invoke, OK: ParserExtensions.Invoke, OK: CommandExtensions.InvokeAsync, OK: CommandExtensions.InvokeAsync, OK: ParseResultExtensions.InvokeAsync, OK: ParserExtensions.InvokeAsync, OK: ParserExtensions.InvokeAsync, OK: ModelBindingCommandHandler.InvokeAsync, OK: RootCommand.ctor(String))"},"cliFramework":"System.CommandLine"},"commands":[{"name":"pub","description":"Command use for publish an dacpac on database server","options":[{"name":"dacpath","recursive":false,"hidden":false,"description":"Dacpac file directory","aliases":["-d"],"arguments":[{"name":"DACPATH","required":true,"arity":{"minimum":1,"maximum":1},"type":"DirectoryInfo"}]},{"name":"NamePattern","recursive":false,"hidden":false,"description":"Name of the file to use. Accept search patterns","aliases":["-f"],"arguments":[{"name":"NAMEPATTERN","required":true,"arity":{"minimum":1,"maximum":1},"type":"String"}]}],"commands":[{"name":"db","options":[{"name":"connectionString","recursive":false,"hidden":false,"description":"Connection string that must be used to access the database","aliases":["-c"],"arguments":[{"name":"CONNECTIONSTRING","required":true,"arity":{"minimum":1,"maximum":1},"type":"String"}]},{"name":"AllowDropBlockingAssemblies","recursive":false,"hidden":false,"arguments":[{"required":false,"arity":{"minimum":0,"maximum":1},"type":"Boolean"}]},{"name":"AllowExternalLanguagePa